By Ma Suping and Cui Huiying, southern weekend journalists

Editor in chief | Cao Haidong

On the afternoon of February 17,2020, the treatment team of the Guangdong medical team in the intensive care unit (ICU) of Wuhan Union Hospital conducted a video consultation with the rear team through an Internet platform. Zhong Nanshan, an academician of the Chinese Academy of Engineering, was involved, predicting the trend of the epidemic, "with the exception of Wuhan, a very rough estimate is that the peak of the epidemic in other parts of the country may occur in mid-to-late February. ".

Zhong Nanshan explains that even a peak does not mean an inflection point is imminent. With the arrival of a wave of migrant workers returning to work, there may be another peak. But for now, with strict inspections and quarantines in place, a new peak is unlikely.

1
"Wuhan has not yet completely stopped human-to-human transmission. "

1

###"Wuhan has not yet completely stopped human-to-human transmission. "

Through model analysis, combined with recent intensified central intervention in the epidemic, the number of new cases outside Hubei has declined for 13 consecutive days. Wuhan has become the most serious epidemic situation in the country. As of 24:00 on February 16, the number of confirmed cases and the case fatality rate in Wuhan accounted for more than 70% of the total number of the country.

"The biggest problem is that Wuhan has not yet completely stopped human-to-human transmission, " Zhong Nanshan said.

On February 12, there were 14840 new cases of coronary pneumonia in Hubei Province, which was 10 times more than the previous day. The reason is that the statistical caliber has changed. Compared with the confirmed cases, these "clinically diagnosed cases" do not have etiological evidence, but have clinical manifestations, imaging features of pneumonia.

Zhong Nanshan believes that if this part of the "clinically diagnosed cases" in the end, will be completely isolated from the normal population, diagnosed with a positive impact on the trend of the epidemic across the country.

To solve this problem, Zhong Nanshan says, it will take two tests: one, a nucleic acid reagent test, to distinguish patients with respiratory disease from others, such as flu, and the other, to improve the accuracy of the nucleic acid test.

At present, Academician Zhong Nanshan's team is developing a new coronavirus IGM antibody rapid test reagent, if approved, will take the lead in Wuhan, "suspected or clinical diagnosis of cases to make clear, in the end is not new coronary pneumonia. ".

2
"critically ill patients in Wuhan are sicker and have a higher mortality rate. "

2

###"critically ill patients in Wuhan are sicker and have a higher mortality rate. "

With the gradual recovery of patients with mild illness discharged from hospital, the burden fell on the shoulders of the Department of Critical Care Medicine. At present, about 18% of all confirmed and hospitalized cases of severe new coronary pneumonia are reported in Wuhan.

Zhong Nanshan, head of the team in Wuhan and deputy director of the Guangzhou Medical University, told southern weekly that since Feb. 6, the team has taken over the 20 beds in the ICU of the Union Medical College West Hospital, at present, no patient extubated achieve spontaneous breathing.

The main difficulty in the treatment of severe NCP is that the disease has different developing rules. With the development of severe NCP, the virus will damage the lung, including the injury of Lung Parenchyma, the secretion of Mucus from the lung blocking the Airway, etc. .
